<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}-{4}{y}=-{79}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{5}{y}={6}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -2. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{2}}{{9}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{2}}}{{9}}{\left({9}{x}+-{4}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{2}}}{{9}}{\left(-{79}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({2}\right)}{x}+{0.88888888888889}{y}={17.555555555556}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{5}{y}={6}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5.8888888888889}{y}={23.555555555556}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{23.555555555556}}{{5.8888888888889}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+-{4}{\left({4}\right)}=-{79}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{\left(-{16}\right)}=-{79}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}=-{79}-{\left(-{16}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}=-{63}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{63}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

